1
00:00:01,429 --> 00:00:02,869
radio announcer:
...WITH TRAFFIC BACKED UP

2
00:00:02,869 --> 00:00:04,829
AT THE HOLLAND TUNNEL,
HEADING INTO LOWER MANHATTAN.

3
00:00:04,829 --> 00:00:06,989
<i>YOU'RE LISTENING
TO THE WAKE-UP CALL ON WXLM,</i>

4
00:00:06,989 --> 00:00:09,469
NEW JERSEY'S NUMBER ONE
TALK RADIO STATION.

5
00:00:10,389 --> 00:00:12,429
MEMORIAL SERVICES
ARE BEING HELD TONIGHT

6
00:00:12,429 --> 00:00:14,309
AT ST. ANTHONY'S CHURCH
IN JERSEY CITY

7
00:00:14,309 --> 00:00:16,109
FOR REGGIE SUAREZ.
[helicopter thumping]

8
00:00:16,109 --> 00:00:18,989
THE 22-YEAR-OLD NATIONAL
GUARDSMAN FROM HOBOKEN

9
00:00:18,989 --> 00:00:21,109
WAS KILLED LAST WEEK BY
A ROADSIDE BOMB JUST OUTSIDE...

10
00:00:21,109 --> 00:00:24,669
[helicopter drowns out radio]

11
00:00:24,669 --> 00:00:26,229
[automatic gunfire]

12
00:00:26,229 --> 00:00:28,109
- HONEY. HONEY?

13
00:00:28,109 --> 00:00:29,949
I GOT YOU NEW UNDERPANTS.

14
00:00:29,949 --> 00:00:32,029
OPRAH SAYS THAT MOST WOMEN
WEAR THEM TOO SMALL.

15
00:00:32,029 --> 00:00:36,189
WHEN I HEARD THAT,
I THOUGHT OF YOU RIGHT AWAY.

16
00:00:36,189 --> 00:00:38,629
- YOU GOT ME BIG GIRL UNDERWEAR.

17
00:00:38,629 --> 00:00:40,149
- MIKE CALLED LAST NIGHT.

18
00:00:40,149 --> 00:00:41,749
- CAN YOU GET
OUT OF MY ROOM?

19
00:00:41,749 --> 00:00:43,469
- ARE YOU GONNA CALL HIM BACK?
- NO.

20
00:00:43,469 --> 00:00:46,309
- OH, RONNIE, GROW UP.
HE'S A MAN. YOU WERE GONE.

21
00:00:46,309 --> 00:00:49,309
DO YOU KNOW HOW MUCH YOUR FATHER
AND I SPENT ON THAT WEDDING?

22
00:00:49,309 --> 00:00:53,069
[door slams]

23
00:00:53,069 --> 00:00:56,389
-  I'M A LITTLE BIT ANXIOUS

24
00:00:56,389 --> 00:01:00,309
I'M A LITTLE BIT SCARED
OF YOU HALF OF THE TIME

25
00:01:00,309 --> 00:01:03,189
[tires screech, crash]

26
00:01:03,189 --> 00:01:04,349
[car alarm blaring]

27
00:01:04,349 --> 00:01:06,869
[woman screams]

28
00:01:06,869 --> 00:01:09,189
- HELP ME, PLEASE, SOMEBODY!

29
00:01:09,189 --> 00:01:12,029
DID SOMEBODY CALL 911?
I'M BLEEDING!

30
00:01:12,029 --> 00:01:13,909
I NEED A DOCTOR NOW!

31
00:01:13,909 --> 00:01:15,029
- I'M A DOCTOR.

32
00:01:15,029 --> 00:01:18,069
- MY HEAD, IT HURTS.
IS IT GONNA SCAR?

33
00:01:18,069 --> 00:01:19,909
- I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

34
00:01:19,909 --> 00:01:21,349
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
JUST APPLY PRESSURE.

35
00:01:21,349 --> 00:01:23,149
- OH, MY--
- DAVID?

36
00:01:23,149 --> 00:01:24,429
WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH HIM?

37
00:01:24,429 --> 00:01:26,109
DAVID! WHAT'S HAPPENING?
WHAT ARE YOU DOING TO HIM?

38
00:01:26,109 --> 00:01:28,069
- I THINK THAT HE MAY HAVE
A TENSION PNEUMOTHORAX.

39
00:01:28,069 --> 00:01:29,509
YOU WANT TO JUMP IN HERE?

40
00:01:29,509 --> 00:01:31,109
- GEE, YOU KNOW, I'M
JUST REALLY A DERMATOLOGIST.

41
00:01:31,109 --> 00:01:32,469
I MOSTLY DO SKIN PEELS.

42
00:01:32,469 --> 00:01:33,949
- WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH HIM?
WAKE UP, BABY!

43
00:01:33,949 --> 00:01:35,309
- HEY, DERMATOLOGIST,
I NEED YOU TO GET ME

44
00:01:35,309 --> 00:01:37,309
A NEEDLE OR A KNIFE AND
SOMETHING TO STERILIZE WITH.

45
00:01:37,309 --> 00:01:39,109
NOW!
- OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

46
00:01:39,109 --> 00:01:41,069
- WHA--

47
00:01:41,069 --> 00:01:42,669
WHAT'S HAPPENING?
WHAT ARE YOU DOING TO HIM?

48
00:01:42,669 --> 00:01:44,349
WHO ARE YOU?
- HEY, LADY, LISTEN.

49
00:01:44,349 --> 00:01:45,549
YOUR BOYFRIEND--
- FIANCE!

50
00:01:45,549 --> 00:01:46,589
- OKAY, FIANCE.

51
00:01:46,589 --> 00:01:48,029
HIS CHEST
IS FILLING UP WITH AIR.

52
00:01:48,029 --> 00:01:50,229
IF I DON'T RELIEVE THE PRESSURE
IN THE NEXT 30 SECONDS,

53
00:01:50,229 --> 00:01:52,149
HE WILL GO INTO CARDIAC ARREST
AND DIE.

54
00:01:52,149 --> 00:01:54,109
NOW HELP ME PULL HIS SHIRT UP.

55
00:01:54,109 --> 00:01:56,349
- IT'S OKAY, BABY.

56
00:01:56,349 --> 00:01:58,469
- DERMATOLOGIST, HOW WE COMING
WITH THAT KNIFE?

57
00:01:58,469 --> 00:02:00,229
- YES. I'M HERE, I'M HERE.

58
00:02:00,229 --> 00:02:01,949
- YOU'RE DOING GOOD.
- THEY'RE ON THEIR WAY.

59
00:02:01,949 --> 00:02:03,109
- OKAY, WHAT NEXT?

60
00:02:03,109 --> 00:02:06,069
- NOW I MAKE A HOLE
IN HIS FIFTH INTERCOSTAL SPACE.

61
00:02:06,069 --> 00:02:07,989
WE'RE GONNA NEED A CHEST TUBE.
HAND ME THAT STRAW.

62
00:02:07,989 --> 00:02:09,029
- WHAT? MAKE A HOLE?

63
00:02:09,029 --> 00:02:12,309
AAH!

64
00:02:12,309 --> 00:02:13,349
[air sputtering]

65
00:02:13,349 --> 00:02:14,989
[deep breath]

66
00:02:14,989 --> 00:02:16,429
[siren wailing]

67
00:02:16,429 --> 00:02:18,909
- HE'S BREATHING.
WHERE DID YOU LEARN TO DO THAT?

68
00:02:18,909 --> 00:02:21,349
- IRAQ.

69
00:02:21,349 --> 00:02:22,429
- WHAT DO WE GOT?

70
00:02:22,429 --> 00:02:23,869
- PATIENT HAD
A TENSION PNEUMOTHORAX.

71
00:02:23,869 --> 00:02:25,509
I DID A NEEDLE DECOMPRESSION
AT THE SCENE.

72
00:02:25,509 --> 00:02:31,069
GET HIM UP TO TRAUMA BAY.
HE NEEDS AN X-RAY.

73
00:02:31,069 --> 00:02:32,429
- WHAT THE HELL'S
GOING ON HERE?

74
00:02:32,429 --> 00:02:33,709
WHO ORDERED ALL THIS?

75
00:02:33,709 --> 00:02:34,709
- ME.

76
00:02:34,709 --> 00:02:36,669
- ON WHAT AUTHORITY?

77
00:02:36,669 --> 00:02:38,429
YOU'RE A NURSE, OKAY?

78
00:02:38,429 --> 00:02:39,589
A NURSE?

79
00:02:39,589 --> 00:02:41,149
I'LL HANDLE IT.

80
00:02:41,149 --> 00:02:42,349
- YOU'RE NOT A DOCTOR?

81
00:02:42,349 --> 00:02:45,789
AFTER ALL THAT,
YOU'RE JUST SOME STUPID NURSE.

82
00:02:45,789 --> 00:02:48,069
IF HE DIES, IF HE HAS
SO MUCH AS A SCAR,

83
00:02:48,069 --> 00:02:49,669
I SWEAR TO GOD,
I WILL SUE YOU,

84
00:02:49,669 --> 00:02:51,429
THE HOSPITAL, AND THE CITY!

85
00:02:51,429 --> 00:02:55,490
[heart monitor beeping]

86
00:03:07,499 --> 00:03:09,499
- SO I GUESS I SHOULD HAVE
JUST LET THE GUY DIE?

87
00:03:09,499 --> 00:03:10,899
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?

88
00:03:10,899 --> 00:03:14,219
- YEAH. THAT'S WHAT WE WANT
HERE AT MERCY HOSPITAL--

89
00:03:14,219 --> 00:03:16,979
TO LET THE GUY DIE.

90
00:03:16,979 --> 00:03:19,099
I BELIEVE THAT'S WHAT IT SAYS
ON THE BROCHURES.

91
00:03:19,099 --> 00:03:20,979
CASE SHOULD HAVE BEEN
IMMEDIATELY TURNED OVER

92
00:03:20,979 --> 00:03:22,299
TO DR. HARRIS.

93
00:03:22,299 --> 00:03:23,819
- HARRIS.

94
00:03:23,819 --> 00:03:26,299
PATIENT'S GOT A BENDY STRAW
STICKING OUT OF HIS CHEST

95
00:03:26,299 --> 00:03:27,659
THAT'S KEEPING HIM ALIVE,

96
00:03:27,659 --> 00:03:30,699
AND ALL THAT HE'S WORRIED ABOUT
IS HIS STUPID EGO.

97
00:03:30,699 --> 00:03:32,699
- YOU MAKE THESE THINGS
PERSONAL, VERONICA.

98
00:03:32,699 --> 00:03:34,139
- NO, I DON'T.

99
00:03:34,139 --> 00:03:36,699
- WHAT ABOUT THE TIME
YOU CALLED HIM A TESTICLE HEAD?

100
00:03:36,699 --> 00:03:38,139
- SCROTUM HEAD.

101
00:03:38,139 --> 00:03:41,339
I CALLED HIM A SCROTUM HEAD.

102
00:03:41,339 --> 00:03:44,019
AND I DIDN'T KNOW THAT
HE WAS STANDING RIGHT THERE.

103
00:03:44,019 --> 00:03:48,419
- I WAS IN A WAR, TOO, YOU KNOW?

104
00:03:48,419 --> 00:03:51,099
HAVE YOU EVER THOUGHT ABOUT
TALKING TO SOMEBODY ABOUT IT?

105
00:03:51,099 --> 00:03:53,699
- I DON'T NEED TO TALK
TO ANYBODY ABOUT IT.

106
00:03:53,699 --> 00:03:55,379
YOU KNOW WHY?

107
00:03:55,379 --> 00:03:58,099
BECAUSE I'M ON DELICIOUS PAXIL.

108
00:03:58,099 --> 00:04:00,019
- WORKING LIKE A CHARM,
I SEE.

109
00:04:00,019 --> 00:04:05,259
[siren wailing]

110
00:04:05,259 --> 00:04:06,259
- SPARE SOME CHANGE?

111
00:04:06,259 --> 00:04:09,539
- OH.

112
00:04:09,539 --> 00:04:15,019
ENERGY BAR?

113
00:04:15,019 --> 00:04:17,059
[thud]

114
00:04:17,059 --> 00:04:19,419
-  RIDING THROUGH THE CITY
ON MY BIKE ALL DAY

115
00:04:19,419 --> 00:04:21,939
'CAUSE THE FILTH
TOOK AWAY MY LICENSE

116
00:04:21,939 --> 00:04:24,059
IT DOESN'T GET ME DOWN,
AND I FEEL OKAY

117
00:04:24,059 --> 00:04:27,099
- HEY, SONIA, YOU GET
THAT MIX C.D. I MADE FOR YOU?

118
00:04:27,099 --> 00:04:29,059
-  EVERYTHING
SEEMS TO LOOK AS IT SHOULD

119
00:04:29,059 --> 00:04:30,179
[cell phone rings]
 BUT I WONDER

120
00:04:30,179 --> 00:04:31,899
WHAT GOES ON BEHIND DOORS

121
00:04:31,899 --> 00:04:33,019
- IS THAT THE LAWYER?
- MM-HMM.

122
00:04:33,019 --> 00:04:34,019
- BUT YOU'RE NOT GONNA ANSWER.

123
00:04:34,019 --> 00:04:35,219
- IT'S CALLED DISCIPLINE.

124
00:04:35,219 --> 00:04:36,579
- YOU LEAVING THE LAWYER
HANGING?

125
00:04:36,579 --> 00:04:37,779
- IT'S CALLED DISCIPLINE.

126
00:04:37,779 --> 00:04:39,419
- I BROUGHT DOUGHNUTS.

127
00:04:39,419 --> 00:04:41,939
LITTLE APPRECIATION FOR
THE BEST NURSES IN THE STATE.

128
00:04:41,939 --> 00:04:45,619
- WOULD YOU LOOK
AT THIS SWEET BOY?

129
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:48,059
- OH, WHAT IN THE HOLY HELL?

130
00:04:48,059 --> 00:04:51,059
- OF ALL THE SMOCKS
IN ALL THE WORLD,

131
00:04:51,059 --> 00:04:52,579
AND SHE HAD TO WALK IN
WEARING THAT.

132
00:04:52,579 --> 00:04:56,099
- HELLO, NURSES.
THIS IS CHLOE PAYNE.

133
00:04:56,099 --> 00:04:57,339
SHE'S STARTING TODAY.

134
00:04:57,339 --> 00:05:00,099
I KNOW YOU'LL TAKE
GOOD CARE OF HER.

135
00:05:00,099 --> 00:05:01,539
[sniffs]

136
00:05:01,539 --> 00:05:03,059
I HAVE TO LEAD ROUNDS.

137
00:05:03,059 --> 00:05:05,979
[call button beeping]

138
00:05:05,979 --> 00:05:08,979
- HI. UM, I JUST WANT TO SAY,

139
00:05:08,979 --> 00:05:11,379
I'M REALLY, REALLY EXCITED
TO BE HERE.

140
00:05:11,379 --> 00:05:12,539
I JUST GOT MY MASTER'S

141
00:05:12,539 --> 00:05:14,379
FROM THE UNIVERSITY
OF PENNSYLVANIA,

142
00:05:14,379 --> 00:05:15,419
AND I AM SO PSYCHED--

143
00:05:15,419 --> 00:05:17,059
- HOLD THAT THOUGHT, FELICITY.

144
00:05:17,059 --> 00:05:19,499
VERONICA, IT'S MRS. BORGHOUSE.
YOU MIGHT WANT TO TAG TEAM.

145
00:05:19,499 --> 00:05:21,139
- I'LL GO WITH YOU.

146
00:05:21,139 --> 00:05:23,379
- CAN I COME?

147
00:05:23,379 --> 00:05:25,059
WHO'S MRS. BORGHOUSE?

148
00:05:25,059 --> 00:05:27,379
- 60-YEAR-OLD WOMAN
WITH END-STAGE LIVER CANCER.

149
00:05:27,379 --> 00:05:28,899
SHE'S BEEN CIRCLING
THE DRAIN FOR MONTHS,

150
00:05:28,899 --> 00:05:30,379
BUT HER FAMILY
WON'T LET HER GIVE UP.

151
00:05:30,379 --> 00:05:33,099
- AW.

152
00:05:33,099 --> 00:05:34,939
POOR THING.

153
00:05:34,939 --> 00:05:39,059
- MM.

154
00:05:39,059 --> 00:05:40,059
- OH!

155
00:05:40,059 --> 00:05:40,939
- AAH!

156
00:05:40,939 --> 00:05:42,499
- I CAN'T EAT THIS FOOD.

157
00:05:42,499 --> 00:05:44,939
I'M IN PAIN, AND I'M PRETTY SURE
I HAVE A BEDSORE.

158
00:05:44,939 --> 00:05:46,219
- OH, NO, YOUR SMOCK.

159
00:05:46,219 --> 00:05:47,979
- IT'S OKAY.
I BROUGHT EXTRAS.

160
00:05:47,979 --> 00:05:49,939
- YOU NURSES, WHAT ARE YOU
GOOD FOR ANYWAY?

161
00:05:49,939 --> 00:05:52,179
- WELL, WE DO TRY AND KEEP
THE DOCTORS FROM KILLING YOU.

162
00:05:52,179 --> 00:05:53,779
- I HAVE TO GO
TO THE BATHROOM.

163
00:05:53,779 --> 00:05:56,739
- OH.

164
00:05:56,739 --> 00:05:57,979
- HAS SHE BEEN FEBRILE TODAY?

165
00:05:57,979 --> 00:06:00,979
- NO, NO FEVER.

166
00:06:00,979 --> 00:06:03,019
- HEY, WHAT ARE THESE DOING
IN SOME OLD GUY'S ROOM?

167
00:06:03,019 --> 00:06:04,099
I BOUGHT THESE FOR YOU.

168
00:06:04,099 --> 00:06:05,939
- YOU CAN'T COME
TO MY WORK ANYMORE.

169
00:06:05,939 --> 00:06:07,859
- IT'S A HOSPITAL.
MAYBE I GOT THE FLU.

170
00:06:07,859 --> 00:06:09,339
HEY, SON.
- HEY, MIKE.

171
00:06:09,339 --> 00:06:11,379
- WOULD YOU LIKE SOME FLOWERS?

172
00:06:11,379 --> 00:06:12,579
- LEAVE ME OUT OF THIS.

173
00:06:12,579 --> 00:06:13,939
DO I REALLY HAVE TO LIE HERE
IN THE SAME ROOM

174
00:06:13,939 --> 00:06:16,259
WITH THIS 12-YEAR-OLD
COVERED IN MY URINE?

175
00:06:16,259 --> 00:06:18,419
- LET'S GET YOU CLEANED UP.

176
00:06:18,419 --> 00:06:20,219
- YOU CAN'T BE HERE.

177
00:06:20,219 --> 00:06:22,379
- [laughs]
YOU BELIEVE HER?

178
00:06:22,379 --> 00:06:24,539
- IF I WERE YOU, I'D LOOK
FOR GREENER PASTURES.

179
00:06:24,539 --> 00:06:25,819
- I KNOW, HUH?

180
00:06:25,819 --> 00:06:28,219
I BEEN BARKING UP THIS TREE
SINCE HIGH SCHOOL.

181
00:06:28,219 --> 00:06:29,539
WHAT ARE YOU DOING LATER?

182
00:06:29,539 --> 00:06:31,579
- I THINK LATER
THEY'RE PUTTING IN A CATHETER.

183
00:06:31,579 --> 00:06:34,219
BUT, SERIOUSLY,
HAVE YOU GOT A JOB?

184
00:06:34,219 --> 00:06:36,339
- YES, MA'AM,
I'M A CONTRACTOR.

185
00:06:36,339 --> 00:06:37,579
I DO ALL RIGHT, TOO.

186
00:06:37,579 --> 00:06:39,659
- THIS IS A PICTURE
OF MY DAUGHTER.

187
00:06:39,659 --> 00:06:42,459
SHE FILLS OUT A SWEATER BETTER
THAN THIS UNGRATEFUL JACKASS,

188
00:06:42,459 --> 00:06:43,939
AND SHE WANTS KIDS.

189
00:06:43,939 --> 00:06:45,739
- OH, OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

190
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:48,779
MIKE, WE'RE SEPARATED.

191
00:06:48,779 --> 00:06:50,939
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO BE MORE CLEAR.

192
00:06:50,939 --> 00:06:52,699
YOU NEED TO LEAVE ME ALONE.

193
00:06:52,699 --> 00:06:55,299
- OKAY, OKAY, I'M SORRY.

194
00:06:55,299 --> 00:06:56,419
I'LL CALL YOU?

195
00:06:56,419 --> 00:07:00,939
- FINE.

196
00:07:00,939 --> 00:07:02,219
NO.

197
00:07:02,219 --> 00:07:03,939
NO! NOT FINE!

198
00:07:03,939 --> 00:07:06,059
WHAT--WHAT DID I JUST SAY?

199
00:07:06,059 --> 00:07:08,019
- NORMALLY,
WE LIKE FOR NEW NURSES

200
00:07:08,019 --> 00:07:09,299
TO HAVE MORE EXPERIENCE,

201
00:07:09,299 --> 00:07:13,499
BUT YOU GRADUATED
TOP OF YOUR CLASS.

202
00:07:13,499 --> 00:07:15,299
ALSO, WE'RE DESPERATE.

203
00:07:15,299 --> 00:07:17,219
- OH, I WON'T DISAPPOINT.

204
00:07:17,219 --> 00:07:19,099
- GOOD.

205
00:07:19,099 --> 00:07:21,699
HERE'S A LITTLE JOB FOR YOU.

206
00:07:21,699 --> 00:07:25,939
MR. WEINTRAUB.

207
00:07:25,939 --> 00:07:27,059
HE'S DEAD.

208
00:07:27,059 --> 00:07:28,419
TURN OFF ALL THE MACHINES.

209
00:07:28,419 --> 00:07:29,819
[heart monitor beeping]

210
00:07:29,819 --> 00:07:32,819
- BUT HE'S STILL ALIVE.
LOOK, HIS HEART IS BEATING.

211
00:07:32,819 --> 00:07:34,139
- NO, HE'S GONE.

212
00:07:34,139 --> 00:07:36,259
TURN OFF ALL THE MACHINES,
CALL THE MORGUE TO GET HIM,

213
00:07:36,259 --> 00:07:43,299
THEN WE'LL FINISH
YOUR START PAPERWORK.

214
00:07:43,299 --> 00:07:45,659
- THAT'S ENOUGH OF THIS!

215
00:07:45,659 --> 00:07:48,659
- COME ON, YOU! COME ON!

216
00:07:48,659 --> 00:07:50,019
I AIN'T DONE
WITH YOU YET!

217
00:07:50,019 --> 00:07:51,619
I AIN'T DONE WITH YOU YET!

218
00:07:51,619 --> 00:07:53,299
YOU'RE DEAD, BITCH!

219
00:07:53,299 --> 00:07:54,979
- HEY, SHUT UP!

220
00:07:54,979 --> 00:07:57,019
HEY, LEAVE THE KID ALONE!

221
00:07:57,019 --> 00:07:58,619
- OKAY, COPS, WAIT OUT THERE.

222
00:07:58,619 --> 00:08:00,739
- HOW'D YOU KNOW I'M A COP?
- IT WAS A LUCKY GUESS.

223
00:08:00,739 --> 00:08:02,619
- HOW ABOUT WE SEPARATE THE GUYS
WHO JUST SHOT EACH OTHER?

224
00:08:02,619 --> 00:08:04,939
- ACTUALLY, I WAS THE ONE
WHO SHOT HIM.

225
00:08:04,939 --> 00:08:06,579
- WHERE'S MY DRIP?

226
00:08:06,579 --> 00:08:07,979
LEG'S ON FIRE!

227
00:08:07,979 --> 00:08:09,179
- SHUT UP, CRYBABY!

228
00:08:09,179 --> 00:08:11,499
- KEEP RUNNING YOUR MOUTH!

229
00:08:11,499 --> 00:08:13,219
- HEY.

230
00:08:13,219 --> 00:08:15,019
DON'T CALL MY MOM, OKAY?

231
00:08:15,019 --> 00:08:17,219
- HOW OLD ARE YOU?

232
